title: mobile: crash on device & simulator: EXC_BAD_ACCESS (code=1, address=0x0)
body:
#### System information

Geth version: `1.6.0 / 1.6.1`
OS & Version: iOS 10
Device: iPhone 6, Simulator

#### Expected behaviour

Should start a node.

#### Actual behaviour

Crashes.
* on device: `EXC_BAD_ACCESS (code=1, address=0x0)`
* on Simulator: `Message from debugger: The LLDB RPC server has crashed.`

#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour

* start a new iOS project in XCode 8.3.1
* add `Geth.framework` either by CocoaPods, or manual version `1.6.0` or `1.6.1-unstable`
* I also manually compiled the framework using `make ios` but the behaviour is the same
* add just the following line: `let bootnodes = GethNewEnodesEmpty()` or call any method from Geth
